<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1015,1040]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
New species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang, 2009" authorityName="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang" authorityYear="2009" box="[626,1271,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinganensis">
<emphasis box="[626,930,1016,1039]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Macromotettix xinganensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng" box="[940,1271,1015,1040]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" refString="Zheng, Z. M., Zhang, H. H. &amp; Dang, L. H. (2009) TWo neW species of Metrodoridae (Orthoptera) from Hainan and GuangXi. Entomotaxonomia, 31 (1), 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2009">Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in disc of pronotum coarse, with numerous protuberances (disc of pronotum smooth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang" authorityYear="2009" box="[1198,1367,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinganensis">
<emphasis box="[1198,1367,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">M. xinganensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); disc of pronotum concave between shoulders (disc of pronotum convex between shoulders in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang" authorityYear="2009" box="[1174,1346,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinganensis">
<emphasis box="[1174,1346,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">M. xinganensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lower margins of fore and middle femora slightly undulate (lower margins of fore and middle femora straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinganensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">M. xinganensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); antennae brown (antennae black in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang" authorityYear="2009" box="[719,891,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinganensis">
<emphasis box="[719,891,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">M. xinganensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lower side of outer part of hind femur black (hind femur dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng, Zhang &amp; Dang" authorityYear="2009" box="[455,624,1197,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xinganensis">
<emphasis box="[455,624,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">M. xinganensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
